      • dbQuery

        default <T> java.util.stream.Stream<T> dbQuery​(Extractor<T> extractor,
                                               SqlStatement sqlStatement)
                                        throws java.sql.SQLException
        Extract results from a SQL query designed to return multiple results. The SQL, and it's optional args are formatted with String.format(String, Object ...) method. Note, Streams are Closeable, and the resultant Stream should be closed when completed to insure database resources involved in the stream are freed.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type extracted and returned in the stream
        Parameters:
        extractor - The extractor to process the ResultSet with
        sqlStatement - The SQL statement
        Returns:
        a stream of the extracted elements
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - if the query or an extraction fails
